claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Table showing pre- and post-vaccination (day 0 and day 28) geometric mean antibody titers (with 95% CI) and response rates (with 95% CI) for placebo, FluBlok, FluBlok PV, and FluBlok NPV groups against three influenza vaccine antigens (A/Solomon Island/3/2006 H1N1, A/Wisconsin/67/2005 H3N2, and B/Malaysia/2506/2004). does not support the claim because the table only presents immunogenicity data comparing FluBlok to placebo and its own formulations, without any information on HA antigen content or a head-to-head comparison with standard-dose flu vaccines. Note: The table lacks details on antigen dosage and does not include a standard-dose vaccine comparator; it focuses solely on placebo and FluBlok arms.
